@node todo "Things to do in Y2k Clock"
This is the first version of Y2k Clock. IF I get enough feedback (by e-mail or
letters) from this program, I might make another version with more features.
Here are some things I might incorporate:

Ę Display of date and weekday.
Ę Alarm-clock system.
Ę Configurable window size and position.
Ę Configurable task priority (now it's -10, just suitable for programs that only
  need attention once a second).
Ę Saved preferences file.
Ę Some kind of GUI (with GadToolsBox, perhaps).
@endnode

@node author "The author of Y2k Clock"
The author of "Y2k Clock" is me, Joona I Palaste. I programmed this program in
DICE C on my Amiga 4000 on the 15th of October 1999.
I am a 22-year-old Finnish man (despite what my first name might sound like!)
who studies at the University of Helsinki, Department of Computer Science. I
only have two major interests in my life:

Ę Amiga« computers.
Ę Transformers« toys.

Currently I have an Amiga 4000/040/40 (32 Mb Fast) and about 80 Transformers
toys, but I'm saving up to another 80 Transformers toys. Hopefully I should get
them before my grandchildren are born.

